-- Hong Kong drawndown mortgage loans rise 5.9 pct in July from June
-- By Christina Lo
-- Wed Aug 27, 2014 06:20AM EDT
-- None



Aug 27 (Reuters) - New mortgage loans drawn down in Hong Kong totalled HK$18.6 billion (2.40 billion US dollar) in July, up 5.9 percent from a month earlier, Hong Kong Monetary Authority (HKMA) data showed on Wednesday.

Following is the breakdown of data from the authority: M/M   July  June Pct Change New loans drawn down (HK$ mln)18,62717,585   5.9 New loans approvals(HK$ mln):- Primary market 6,747 4,833  39.6   - Secondary market  17,75216,669   6.5   - Refinancing3,787 3,545   6.8   TOTAL   28,28625,047  12.9No. of applications (cases)   12,72811,442  11.2  Outstanding loans (HK$ mln): 940,029   934,078   0.6   - Delinquency ratio (pct) 0.03  0.02  - Rescheduled loan ratio (pct)0.00  0.00   Proportion of new mortgage loans   priced with reference to:   - best lending rates (pct)   17.4*  21.0  -3.6   - HIBOR (Hong Kong interbank